    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Colt Keith** (64.05) and **Trea Turner** (61.51) serving as our primary offensive engines. **Colt Keith** commands the top of the board thanks to a premium #3 spot in the order against Sproat, whose 4.17 xERA provides the softest landing spot among our high-confidence starters. **Trea Turner** remains an essential start; despite facing a capable arm in Cabrera, his elite leadoff position (+10% efficiency boost) ensures he maximizes every plate appearance, and his threat on the basepaths is critical given our heavy weighting toward SB scarcity. While **Kyle Schwarber** (58.75) narrowly missed the \"Strong\" tier, his elite 0.402 xwOBA remains the most reliable indicator of potential power production despite a challenging matchup.\n\nOur decision-making process for the utility spots was heavily influenced by park factors and efficiency floors. **Caleb Durbin** (52.24) earns the nod over **Carson Benge** (36.41) largely due to a park boost (+7%) and a more favorable hitting environment. **Carson Benge** landed well below our 40.0 floor, failing to overcome a significant penalty for his #9 spot in the order and a tough matchup against Ryan. We are closely monitoring the status of **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, whose base profile (60.83) suggests he should be a regular, but he remains benched today due to current lineup uncertainty and a negative platoon split against S\u00e1nchez.\n\nWarning flags persist for the bottom of our order. **Hyeseong Kim** (41.56) and **Josh Smith** (41.42) are hovering precariously above the bench floor. **Hyeseong Kim** faces the dual threat of a sub-3.20 xERA pitcher and a brutal #8 spot in the lineup, though his efficiency is salvaged slightly by the potential for SB opportunities against a slow pitcher delivery. Meanwhile, **Gary Sanchez** (45.04) and **Dillon Dingler** (44.82) are locked into mid-range scores; they are necessary plays for positional coverage, but neither possess a favorable enough matchup to elevate their production projections beyond the marginal tier. We will continue to evaluate **Yordan Alvarez** and **Junior Caminero** on their next scheduled game day to provide the offensive spark currently missing from the back end of this lineup.",
